	<h1>@OnEvent</h1>

	If you prefer, you can annotate event handler methods with <em>@OnEvent</em> rather than use the "on" naming convention.

	<div class="eg"> 
		Count = ${count}.<br/> 
		<t:eventlink t:event="add" t:context="literal:1">Add 1</t:eventlink><br/> 
		<t:eventlink t:event="add" t:context="literal:2">Add 2</t:eventlink><br/>
		<t:eventlink t:event="clear">Clear</t:eventlink>
	</div>	  

	References:	
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.3/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/annotations/OnEvent.html">@OnEvent</a>, 
